<title type="html"><![CDATA[8/3(Sat.)'Fridays for Future': What next?/CAL finds data on cigarette preorders dating to 2006(Host: Ivonne)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=304&amp;p=320#p320"><![CDATA[
8/3(Sat.)'Fridays for Future': What next?/CAL finds data on cigarette preorders dating to 2006(Host: Ivonne)<br /><br />Article 1: 'Fridays for Future': What next?<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.dw.com/en/fridays-for-future-what-next/a-49292611">https://www.dw.com/en/fridays-for-futur ... a-49292611</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Question:<br />1) Young European take to the streets in Fridays for Future protests. What do you think about that? Is that too serious?<br />2) Environment issue might not be hot in Taiwan. Many issues in article is similar to Taiwanese situation. Please share that to your partner.<br />3) A concept is mentioned in the article. Consumerism is one of reason we have to fight. (Consumerism is a social and economic order that encourages the acquisition of goods and services in ever-increasing amounts.) Do you have tips to consume less? Or to produce rubbish less?<br /><br />Article 2: CAL finds data on cigarette preorders dating to 2006<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/front/archives/2019/07/29/2003719526">http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/front/a ... 2003719526</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Question:<br />1) Suppose you were one of the National Security Bureau on the same trip, if  you preorder the cigarette or not ? Why?<br />2) Cigarette Smuggling Scandal Reveals what kind the problems in Taiwan.<br />3) do you know how much the other same scandals from past decades?<br /><br />Agenda<br />7:00 ~ 7:30 pm greetings &amp; free talk <br />7:30 ~ 8:15 pm guests introduced &amp; first session discussion <br />8:15 ~ 8:45 pm presentation, sharing the article &amp; other experiences <br />8:45 ~ 9:30 pm second session discussion<br /><br />Position: Dante coffee Shop (丹堤咖啡), MRT板南線 - 新埔站2號出口, next to 7-Seven, <br />板橋民生路二段237 號, <br />Time: PM 7:00-9:30, <br />a minimum charge of Dante coffee for Royal English club attendant NT$80 (丹提低消80元)<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500.請帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=12531">Danny Lin</a> — Thu Aug 01, 2019 1:53 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
